net.sf.mmm.util.query.api.feature

Interface FeatureValues<SELF extends FeatureValues<SELF>>

  • Type Parameters:
    SELF - the generic type of this query itself (this) for fluent API calls.
    All Superinterfaces:
    StatementFeature

    public interface FeatureValues<SELF extends FeatureValues<SELF>>
extends StatementFeature
    StatementFeature for a Statement allowing a VALUES clause. For each invocation of value(pI, vI) a value binding is added so in the end the resulting SQL fragment will be: 
     (p1, p2, ..., pN) VALUES (v1, v2, ..., vN)
    Since:
    8.0.0
    Author:
    hohwille

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <V> SELF value(PropertyPath<V> path, V value)
      Adds a value binding setting the given PropertyPath to the given value.

    • Method Detail

      • value

        <V> SELF value(PropertyPath<V> path,
               V value)
        Adds a value binding setting the given PropertyPath to the given value.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the generic type of the value.
        Parameters:
        path - the PropertyPath for the value to assign that will be added to the bracket before the keyword.
        value - the literal value to assign that will be added to the bracket after the keyword.
        Returns:
        this query instance for fluent API calls.
